Question-2: State the business question you will investigate using this dataset.

A company’s capacity to stay competitive is increasingly threatened by employee turnover. Finding, acquiring, and educating new personnel is a very expensive effort. It is cheaper for a company to keep its present workforce. To retain employees for the long run, an organization must create a favorable work environment. What characteristics (or predictors) will boost this individual’s chances of staying with the company? This information might be utilized in a prediction model to assess the possibility of an employee quitting the organization. The term “Attrition” will serve as my project’s primary target variable.

Question-3: What could be the most simple, easiest answer to your business question? To answer this, sort your data lowest to highest in terms of your target variable and interpret the lowest row, and highest row. If you have a categorical target, create a table showing the most and least frequent categories.

The majority class as per the below table is 0 (Staying) and the minority class is 1 (Leaving).

##   Attrition    n
## 1        No 1477
## 2       Yes  199

Question-4: State the method you plan to use to answer the business question in your project. Why?

I plan to use Logistic regression in this project. An employee’s response to the question of whether or not he or she plans to remain with the organization is always binary: yes (staying) or no (leaving). Employee Attrition, our dependent variable, is clearly a categorical variable. The term “LOGISTIC REGRESSION” must be used since we are dealing with a classification issue.
